{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"19fa9bb1-c456-49f2-9d5a-2e7b5f847cb7","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" in results with your reason message visible in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"efd66464-6bfd-464f-be53-5a79b8024991","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":228,"requestId":"5C28:96AFF:1B9682:2221F6:69F54EFB"},"id":"b60254fb-0f7d-4bcd-973b-4c1335c8f09c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:10:24.932Z","parentId":"d3663463-3df2-4032-a7fa-db95a106ca5e"}
